parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition System Failure (TFI Ignition Module and Distributor)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch on fire, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: unusual burning smells or smoke from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, as well as damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: unusual burning smells or smoke from the engine compartment
sparks or flames visible from the ignition switch area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and pose a risk to the safety of the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: smoke or flames visible under the hood

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine coolant and oil leaks, leading to overheating, engine damage, and potentially a fire.
Failure of the Quik Connect hose can cause coolant leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially a fire.
The sudden and unexpected lockup of the right front brake can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The right front brake locks up when applying the foot brake
no braking on the other three wheels
inability to stop the vehicle using the foot brake
requiring the use of the hand brake and steering to avoid collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Failure due to Automatic Adjuster Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes to engage can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increase the risk of accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear brakes fail to engage
automatic adjuster failure to make adjustments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine head gasket can cause coolant and oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potentially a vehicle fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: white smoke or steam coming from the engine
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan motor can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage, and potentially a vehicle fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: loud noises from the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack-and-pinion steering system can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: grinding or clunking noises when turning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lockup of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: vehicle stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel ventilation system can cause smoke or fumes to enter the cabin, potentially distracting the driver and leading to accidents.
symptoms: Blue smoke or fumes coming from the instrument panel vents
unusual odors or smells inside the cabin.
